The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Aug. 31: The Prime Minister?s task force on drugs has recommended fixing a ceiling on prices, which could be flexible and linked to the wholesale price index. Sources informed that the task force headed by Pranob Sen has said ?the kind of price control being practised at present is not acceptable as it blocked the entry of new drugs?. The panel also wanted the drugs price control order to be made into an act. 

 Calcutta, Aug. 31: Jessop amp; Co today said the Board for Industrial and Financial Reconstruction has approved its plan to reduce the capital base. ?We will reduce the capital from Rs 95.07 crore to Rs 9.50 crore by bringing down the face value of each Rs 10 paid up share to Re 1 per share,? CMD P.K. Ruia said.

 New Delhi, Aug. 31: Andhra Pradesh chief minister Y.S. Rajashekhara Reddy has said Volkswagen?s project would go ahead in the state as matters have been sorted out.

 New Delhi, Aug. 31: The government today extended the date for annual filing of returns on tax deducted at source and quarterly statements to September 30. The earlier deadline was June 30.

 Mumbai, Aug. 31: Dishman Pharmaceuticals amp; Chemicals today said it would split equity shares in the 1:5 ratio.




